an>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont\">rightCont</a></span></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont_eq_of_nhdsGT_eq_bot","kind":"theorem","line":299,"name":"MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont_eq_of_nhdsGT_eq_bot","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.lean#L299-L302"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont_apply\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Filtration</span>.<span class=\"name\">rightCont_apply</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/PartialOrder.html#PartialOrder\">PartialOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Order/Basic.html#OrderTopology\">OrderTopology</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration\">Filtration</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont\">rightCont</a></span></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">if</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhdsWithin\">nhdsWithin</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/Defs.html#Set.Ioi\">Set.Ioi</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.NeBot\">NeBot</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">then</a> <span class=\"fn\">⨅ (<span class=\"fn\">j</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\">⨅ (_ : <span class=\"fn\">j</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#GT.gt\">&gt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span></span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span></span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">else</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont_apply","kind":"theorem","line":294,"name":"MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont_apply","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.lean#L294-L297"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.«term_₊»\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Filtration</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_₊»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a filtration `𝓕`, its **right continuation** is the filtration `𝓕₊` defined as follows:\n- If `i` is isolated on the right, then `𝓕₊ i := 𝓕 i`;\n- Otherwise, `𝓕₊ i := ⨅ j > i, 𝓕 j`.\nIt is sometimes simply defined as `𝓕₊ i := ⨅ j > i, 𝓕 j` when the index type is `ℝ`. In the\ngeneral case this is not ideal however. If `i` is maximal for instance, then `𝓕₊ i = ⊤`, which\nis inconvenient because `𝓕₊` is not a `Filtration ι m` anymore. If the index type\nis discrete (such as `ℕ`), then we would have `𝓕 = 𝓕₊` (i.e. `𝓕` is right-continuous) only if\n`𝓕` is constant.\n\nTo avoid requiring a `TopologicalSpace` instance on `ι` in the definition, we endow `ι` with\nthe order topology `Preorder.topology` inside the definition. Say you write a statement about\n`𝓕₊` which does not require a `TopologicalSpace` structure on `ι`,\nbut you wish to use a statement which requires a topology (such as `rightCont_apply`).\nThen you can endow `ι` with the order topology by writing\n```lean\n  letI := Preorder.topology ι\n  haveI : OrderTopology ι := ⟨rfl⟩\n``` ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.«term_₊»","kind":"def","line":290,"name":"MeasureTheory.Filtration.«term_₊»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.lean#L290-L290"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Filtration</span>.<span class=\"name\">rightCont</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/PartialOrder.html#PartialOrder\">PartialOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration\">Filtration</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration\">Filtration</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a filtration `𝓕`, its **right continuation** is the filtration `𝓕₊` defined as follows:\n- If `i` is isolated on the right, then `𝓕₊ i := 𝓕 i`;\n- Otherwise, `𝓕₊ i := ⨅ j > i, 𝓕 j`.\nIt is sometimes simply defined as `𝓕₊ i := ⨅ j > i, 𝓕 j` when the index type is `ℝ`. In the\ngeneral case this is not ideal however. If `i` is maximal for instance, then `𝓕₊ i = ⊤`, which\nis inconvenient because `𝓕₊` is not a `Filtration ι m` anymore. If the index type\nis discrete (such as `ℕ`), then we would have `𝓕 = 𝓕₊` (i.e. `𝓕` is right-continuous) only if\n`𝓕` is constant.\n\nTo avoid requiring a `TopologicalSpace` instance on `ι` in the definition, we endow `ι` with\nthe order topology `Preorder.topology` inside the definition. Say you write a statement about\n`𝓕₊` which does not require a `TopologicalSpace` structure on `ι`,\nbut you wish to use a statement which requires a topology (such as `rightCont_apply`).\nThen you can endow `ι` with the order topology by writing\n```lean\n  letI := Preorder.topology ι\n  haveI : OrderTopology ι := ⟨rfl⟩\n``` ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont","kind":"def","line":254,"name":"MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.lean#L254-L288"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.rightCont_def\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Filtration</span>.<span class=\"name\">rightCont_def</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.htm